content:
How do I calculate the total capacitance of two capacitors connected in series with capacitance values of C1 = 10 microfarads and C2 = 15 microfarads, respectively? Please provide the calculation using the following formula:
Ctotal = \frac{C1 \cdot C2}{C1 + C2}
where Ctotal is the total capacitance in microfarads, C1 and C2 are the capacitance values of the two capacitors in microfarads.
